Description: Wall sherd of North Ionian pottery cup or bowl; orange clay with some silver mica; interior: glazed orange with added red band lined in white; exterior: glazed at top, broad band and thin band below; lower wall reserved; inscription lightly cut on lower wall.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.360)
